com.gl.vn.me.ko.sample.instrumentation.example.proxy

Class MethodInterceptorExampleB

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.gl.vn.me.ko.sample.instrumentation.example.proxy.MethodInterceptorExampleB
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Callback, MethodInterceptor

    final class MethodInterceptorExampleB
extends Object
implements MethodInterceptor
    This class is a method interceptor that is used by BigDecimalProxyFactoryExampleB to create CGLib-proxy objects.

    Instantiability: explicit instantiation is forbidden; singleton (see INSTANCE field).
    Mutability: immutable.
    Thread safety: thread-safe.

    • Method Detail

      • intercept

        @Nullable
public final Object intercept(Object proxyObject,
                                        Method method,
                                        Object[] methodArgs,
                                        MethodProxy proxyMethod)
                                 throws Throwable
        Invokes the original method of proxied class. Negates the value returned from the original method if this value is of type BigDecimal.
        Specified by:
        intercept in interface MethodInterceptor
        Parameters:
        proxyObject - Enhanced (proxy) object.
        method - Intercepted method.
        methodArgs - Array of arguments (primitive types are wrapped).
        proxyMethod - Used to invoke original method (not enhanced method, that will not be intercepted). May be called as many times as needed.
        Returns:
        Result of the original method invocation (can be null) or negated value of the original result if it's of type BigDecimal.
        Throws:
        Throwable - If something goes wrong.
